        "subject": "LU-4783 mgs: start params log during mgs setup(fortestonly)",
        "message": "LU-4783 mgs: start params log during mgs setup(fortestonly)\n\nParams llog was introduced by LU-3155 to set parameters permanently\nwith lctl \"set_param -P\" instead of \"conf_param\". But in a newly\nmounted filesystem, it won't be created automatically until \"lctl\nset_param -P\" is called.\nThis patch is to start params llog during mgs initialization so that\nthe server can make a local copy successfully during its setup, and\nthe confusing console error message \"LustreError: 13a-8: Failed to get\nMGS log params and no local copy.\" can be quieted.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Emoly Liu <emoly.liu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If1ed74df5921d6bd1f0e974883742552718fd8ce\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
